ed Kingdom","Southowram, Yorkshire, England":"Southowram, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hemingway","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Yorkshire): habitational name from an unidentified place, recorded only in the surname, but which was probably in Southowram (Yorkshire). The origin of the placename may derive from the Old English personal name <i>Hemma</i> + Old English connective <i>-ing-</i> or the groupname suffix <i>-ingas</i> (genitive <i>-inga-</i>) + <i>weg</i> ‘way, path, road’."],"variants":[{"name":"Hemmingway","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lancashire): variant of   Hemingway  ."]},{"name":"Hemenway","meanings":["English (Yorkshire): variant of   Hemingway  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"Samuel","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name (Hebrew <i>Shemuel</i>), possibly meaning ‘He (God) has hearkened’ (presumably to the prayers of a mother for a son). It may also be understood as a contracted form of Hebrew <i>sha'ulme'el</i> meaning ‘asked of God’. In the case of Samuel the son of Hannah, this would be more in keeping with his mother's statement ‘Because I have asked him of the Lord’ (1 Samuel 1:20). Living in the 11th century  bc , Samuel was a Hebrew judge and prophet of the greatest historical importance, who established the Hebrew monarchy, anointing as king both Saul and, later, David. In the Authorized Version two books of the Old Testament are named after him, although in Roman Catholic and Orthodox versions of the Bible they are known as the first and second Book of Kings. The story of Samuel being called by God while still a child serving in the house of Eli the priest (1 Samuel 3) is of great vividness and has moved countless generations. In England and America the name was particularly popular among the 16th-century Puritans and among Nonconformists from the 17th to the 19th century. It became fashionable again in the 1990s."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Samuel Hemingway was born in 1555, his father, John Hemingway, was 35 and his mother, Agnes Anne Mawd, was 17. He married Ruth Copeland in 1602. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1602, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 47."},"et":{"1555–1602":"1555–1602","1555–1603":"1555–1603","1603–1678":"1603–1678","1520–1578":"1520–1578","1538–1575":"1538–1575","1602":"1602","1678":"1678","1578":"1578","1555":"1555","26 October 1556":"26. oktoober 1556","1575":"1575","1520":"1520","16 July 1575":"16. juuli 1575","5 October 1578":"5. oktoober 1578","1538":"1538","1603":"1603","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Southowram, Yorkshire, England":"Southowram, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1555–1602":"1555–1602","1555–1603":"1555–1603","1603–1678":"1603–1678","1520–1578":"1520–1578","1538–1575":"1538–1575","1602":"1602","1678":"1678","1578":"1578","1555":"1555","26 October 1556":"26. lokakuuta 1556","1575":"1575","1520":"1520","16 July 1575":"16. heinäkuuta 1575","5 October 1578":"5. lokakuuta 1578","1538":"1538","1603":"1603","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Southowram, Yorkshire, England":"Southowram, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1555–1602":"1555–1602","1555–1603":"1555–1603","1603–1678":"1603–1678","1520–1578":"1520–1578","1538–1575":"1538–1575","1602":"1602","1678":"1678","1578":"1578","1555":"1555","26 October 1556":"26 octobre 1556","1575":"1575","1520":"1520","16 July 1575":"16 juillet 1575","5 October 1578":"5 octobre 1578","1538":"1538","1603":"1603","Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Southowram, Yorkshire, England":"Southowram, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Samuel Hemingway est né en 1555, 